This is not a game. You search through video clips to piece together a story. That is all. There is no end where you see the entire story or have the true story revealed. The entire game is to guess search words to find all the clips. This might have worked as a small puzzle within an adventure game.

content: Not a game per se but a very interesting concept. You uncover the story by clicking on police files and slowly but surely what's happening emerges (or does it?).  A very original game and worth it for that. But be prepared for a bit of repetition of clips to get to the final unseen ones. And the story is not fully resolved and it's up to you to decide what's really going on - which may be a good or bad thing for different people.
This is not a game. Just a series of clips. Feel cheated out of $, was misled by positive reviews.
More like searching google for videos than playing a game. Ending is vague and useless
Very good story, fun and intriguing. I was slightly disappointed in the lack of a definitive ending, but a solid, unique game all around.
Thriller classic!

Navigate through old archived interview clips to find whodunnit in this detective game. All the clips are transcribed and can be searched using certain keywords. You can find clues to your next keyword by watching the clips themselves. One clip gives you clues to the next keyword that leads you to the next clip and so on.  It was a fascinating experience piecing together this story little by little. I admit I did have to YouTube to understand the entire story, but it's only because I didn't want to put the effort into arranging the story in my head in chronology.
Love the fact we are FINALLY getting this on Android. Yay!
Such a great game

For me, a story based game is successful when my memories of playing it have blended into its world.  When I think back to playing this game, my past self isn't sitting on the toilet tapping an android tablet - he's in a police station tapping away at the keyboard of a dusty old computer.

Interesting and novel gameplay idea. Intriguing story. Sometimes frustrating that you don't know the exact term you need to search for to get the appropriate video, but when it goes it's very enjoyable

content: Unfortunately it performs so poorly on Android N on my Pixel C it's unplayable. I'll wait for the update that is sure to come.

I was captivated by Her Story until it became evident that it is not a game and that the objective is to sort through clips to understand what happened. The major revelations lacked weight and the overall experience was boring instead of exciting. Unfortunately, watching the story as revealed by short unsorted clips feels less and less interesting as you encounter more significant moments... like watching clips of Forensic Files at random. This idea had a lot of potential, but sadly was poorly executed.

I'm kind of annoyed I paid for this game. I don't really feel like it was worth the $4. It was interesting but so short. I got a couple days of play out of it and that's it. I'd expect to pay less than that for a game I would play for years. Shame.

content: INTELLIGENT AND VERY CREATIVE GAMEPLAY!
